CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 11, 1967, pg. 12, reads: "Three in a row - Dominating the City League in a manner that has not been duplicated in more than two decades, the Schenley High School champions of 1965,1966 and 1967 pose for a Courier cameraman.  Standing - from left - Raderick [Roderick] Horne, Henry Brandon, Robert Evans, Coach Willard Fisher, Ruben Eberhardt, Bernard Jenks.  Bending - Edward Gibson, Montel Brundage, and Willie Clay.  Seated - Thomas Hawkins, Willie Clay, Kenneth Durett [Durrett]. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School basketball players seated from left: Paul Sheard, Willie Clay, #54 Kenneth Durrett, Dana Turnipseed; bending: Edward "Petey" Gibson, Montel Brundage, Rick Ellison; standing: Jim Lasane, #22 Roderick Horne, #40 Henry Brandon, Edward Fullum, #34 Robert "Bob" Evans, coach Willard Fisher, Sherman Turner, #30 Bill Boyce, and "Dizzy" on right, in Civic Arena
